Is not that the Bridge of Sighs?
Yeah, I am pretty sure it was in the guidebook.
Up ahead is the Bridge of Sighs.
Because it is so beautiful it makes you want to sigh!
No, its name actually comes from Manhome, back when prisoners had to cross this bridge...
It is the sea!...after receiving their sentence at Doge's Palace, and they would let out a deep sigh when they saw...
I am glad we came here.
Geez, could she be any more stiff?
It looks like she has a clothes hanger for shoulders.
I had such a good time.
At any rate, it seems like she was able to satisfy her customers.
President Aria, please hold it in!
Alice will notice we are here!
We just happened to be passing by...
We just happened to see you while you were working and decided to watch...
You two... watched me... while I was working...
You seem to have managed it okay!
It was very thoughtful of you to back up, so that gentleman could see those cats.
Athena would have done the same...
You have been watching me for that long?
Spying on me is really not allowed!
Please tell me honestly what you thought!
Well, my thought was that you looked like a toy robot.
You know there is no time to be depressed, right?
Why do not we have a moon-gazing party tonight?
It is fall now, and the weather's nice today.
I am sure the moon will look really beautiful!
This... is the first time I have ever been moon-gazing.
It is not a tradition we have here on Aqua.
Why are we having dumplings at our moon-gazing party?
They are supposed to be symbolic of Manhome's moon.
Eating two at once is no fair!
Then, I will have four at once!
President Maa, President Aria's pudgy-wudgy tummy is not a moon-gazing dumpling!
This is the brown rice tea that the postman recommended.
The season when warm drinks taste great is finally here, is not it?
Come to think of it, Al is late, is not he?
Since when was Al supposed to join us?
Was not the moon-gazing party just for the three of us?
A-An event about the moon and stars would not be complete without Al, right?
Maybe he could teach us a thing or two.
Since you were not there that night when we all saw the meteor shower,
I invited Al so you could catch up!
I bet he is late because of work again.
He might be lost somewhere, too.
Thank you very much for inviting me today.
Gazing up at the moon like this...
Tomorrow, if I can be like the moon and keep this sense of tranquility,
I think I will be able to do much better.
Alice, would you like some more tea?
I had to stay late and work.
Well, if there is one good thing about me being late...
It is fine, it is fine!
It is my fault for weighing so much, after all...
It is a good thing the city's wells have dried up and are no longer in use, but...
A long time ago, before the city had a water system...
It must have been lively when housewives gathered to fetch water in the morning, and again at night.
I bet there were a lot of wellside gossip meetings!
And why did you jump down?
Go get Junior, on the double!
She is still a kitten, after all.
President Maa is a fine Aqua Cat that can understand human language!
I have no doubt... she will get... Junior... to come... for us...
At any rate, you are the only one who can help us!
Do you really think we can count on her?
What a strange moon-gazing this turned out to be...
I wonder why the moon revolves around Aqua?
It is because of the forces of attraction and repulsion.
As I have explained before, the force of attraction...
Unable to get closer or move farther away, the moon just goes around and around.
The outer moon is used as a space station, among other things, by several different fields of study.
They mine minerals and perform chemical experiments which can only be done in a vacuum.
Back on Manhome, it is said their moon's craters resemble many different shapes.
For example, some say it looks like a crab with huge claws, or an old woman knitting,
or a lion, or a woman's profile, or rabbits pounding rice cakes...
Ah, speaking of rabbits, that reminds me!
I hear the Rabbit-Pounded Rice Cakes sold at the space station are really tasty!
I have been wanting to try them, so I mail-ordered some the other day.
They also come with a haiku collection book about the moon, so I am really looking forward to it!
At any rate, it is quite dark in this well, is not it?
Gnomes are always working in the dark and can see really well at night, so...
Since there is no sunlight, the lighting infrastructure underground is quite advanced...
Big Sis is here with you!
The inner moon is approximately 1.8 times bigger than the outer moon,
and it flies around in a geostationary orbit over Aqua.
The inner moon completes its orbit around Aqua in under eight hours...
That distance is just 1165th of the distance between Manhome and its moon.
It is really close, is not it?
The small moon that got too close...
It may seem like it is just the moon that is affected by Aqua...
So Aqua is under the influence of the moon, as well.
I am so glad we found you, Aika.
I cannot believe you fell down into a well like that.
Is that how you talk to your rescuers?
I am grateful to President Maa.
By the way, when did you two get there?

It is because of centrifugal force!
If you are afraid of getting close and just flail around, it makes you hungry!
It is the force of attraction.
